99% of gymgoers today would associate barbell squats with drinking milk/GOMAD, but ~15 years ago squats actually used to go together with oats. The meme was that to get big you had to squat and eat oats. "Squats and oats". People photoshopped the Quaker oats guy with the barbell.

Completely different era of fitness culture. Almost no one lifting today remembers this stuff. It was before my day too, I just remember still seeing the phrase as something most people knew about on /fit/ and such. Milk is obviously superior though so not a bad development...

It's so weird how AI is obviously pretty useful as library software for stuff like summing up needlessly long studies, searching the internet quickly, etc. but the cultural AI proponents are obsessed with retarded concepts like making characters out of it or generating paintings.

Like for some reason they don't care about the actual useful applications like searching thousands of books in a second for some concept/keyword but keep insisting on idiotic bad sci-fi ideas about "AI friends" or generating videos that no one wants or needs (or will ever use).

Like the more it's like a library computer from a Gene Wolfe novel that can collect, "analyze", categorize, and sum up 1000 PubMed studies in a few minutes, the more useful it is. But the loudest AI people are obsessed with tiresome "creative" applications which are embarrassing.
It's wonderful in that sphere, I think there is lots of room, there are probably a lot of subtle changes undetectable by human eyes with diagnostic potential
